## `<file-level: imports and records>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-locks-1 -->

### Purpose
In-memory advisory lock manager implementing three distinct lock namespaces (POSIX, OFD, BSD flock). No disk persistence â€” a daemon crash releases all locks, which is POSIX-compliant. The three namespaces are independent: a POSIX lock does not conflict with a BSD flock, and so on.

### Implementation Notes

```python
from dataclasses import dataclass, field
from typing import Literal

from sqlite_fs.errors import LockConflict
from sqlite_fs.types import LockOp, FlockOp, LockQuery


@dataclass
class _Record:
    """Internal lock record. Not exposed publicly."""
    kind: Literal["posix", "ofd", "flock"]
    type: Literal["shared", "exclusive"]
    owner: int              # pid for posix; fd_id for ofd/flock
    start: int
    length: int             # 0 = to EOF/infinity
```

A single list of `_Record` per inode is sufficient for v1 â€” load is small (<1000 records per inode in realistic workloads), and scanning is O(n) per operation. Optimize only if measurements demand.

