## `LockManager.posix_getlk(self, inode: int, fd_id: int, pid: int, start: int, length: int) -> LockQuery | None`
<!-- checksum: locks-6 -->

### Purpose
F_GETLK: query whether a lock could be acquired at `(start, length)` for the given pid. Does not modify state. If acquirable â†’ return `None`. Else â†’ return a `LockQuery` describing the conflicting lock.

### Postconditions
- Returns `None` iff no `kind="posix"` record held by a different pid overlaps the query range.
- Otherwise returns `LockQuery(type, pid, start, length)` describing the first conflicting record.

### Test Strategy
`test_locks Â§ test_getlk_returns_none_if_free`, `Â§ test_getlk_returns_conflicting_lock`.

